column6:
PLC Major Fault
All operations have stopped

The PLC has encountered a major error and halted all operations.
Any errors must be resolved prior to resetting the PLC.

All operations have stopped

column6:

Should Not Be Lowered.
column7: Cylinder sensor is reporting that the cylinder is in a position that it should not be in. Check if product guides are lowered and are in place. Next, check that the cylinder has moved off/away from the sensor. If so, check the sensor for damage and replace as needed.

column6:
DM 1 (Top)
Classification Timestamp Not Updating
column7:
DM 1 classification software has not sent the PLC a timestamp/heartbeat within a specified amount of time. Check Spec 1 and Vis 1 computers are running the classification software and that it's PLC tracking time is synchronized with the PLC.
Restarting the computers may solve the issue.
column9:
F070   DM 1 (Top)
Classification Timestamp Not Updating
Device U2-1     IP Address: 10.0.1.19

column6:
DM 1 (Top)
Classification Timestamp Offset Error
column7: DM 1 classification timestamp is out of range by more than a specified amount. Execute a calibration to re-synchronize the computer's clock with the PLC and Control Computer. If the issue persists, contact the PPO service team.
column9:
F071   DM 1 (Top)
Classification Timestamp Offset Error
Device U2-1     IP Address: 10.0.1.19

column6:
Spec 1 (Top)
Too Many Consecutive Reject Message Errors
column7: Spec 1 Computer has sent several invalid reject messages to the PLC. Contact the PPO Service team for assistance.
column9:
F072   Spec 1 (Top)
Too Many Consecutive Reject Message Errors
Device U2-1     IP Address: 10.0.1.19

column6:
Spec 1 (Top)
Calibration Failure
Error Code: /*N:10 {[PLC]C_FAULT_SPEC_1} NOFILL DP:0*/
column7:
Spec 1 Computer has detected one of the following errors during calibration. The system has attempted to calibrate multiple times and the issue persists.
Reason codes (bitwise):
Bit 0 - Brightness level too low. This may indicate the lamps need to be changed.
Bit 1 - Bright/Dark levels are too close to each other. This may indicate the shutter is failing.
Bit 2 - Too many dark underflowing lines during the darkness calibration.
Bit 3 - Dark level is higher than the bright level. This may indicate that the shutter position has been swapped.
column9:
F073   Spec 1 (Top)
Calibration Failure
Error Code: /*N:10 {[PLC]C_FAULT_SPEC_1} NOFILL DP:0*/
Device U2-1     IP Address: 10.0.1.19

column6:
Spec 1 Computer
NTP Time Synchronization Error
column7:
Spec 1 Computer's NTP clock is not synchronized with the NTP clock on the Control Computer. Perform a calibration.
This issue has been detected by the Spec 1 Computer.
If the issue persists after a calibration:
-Shutdown and restart all computers
-Contact PPO's team for assistance.
column9:
F074   Spec 1 Computer
NTP Time Synchronization Error
Device U2-1     IP Address: 10.0.1.19

column7:

- Inspect the wiring for damage.

Communication Error
column7:
The PLC is reporting a communication error with the VFD controller. Check the following:
- Ensure the VFD is powered on and does not have any faults (F073 is ok)
- Ethernet connection between the VFD and PLC
- Check that there is no other devices on the network with the same IP address
- Power cycle the VFD controller.

column6:
TDK Power Supply
Communication Error
column7:
PLC is unable to communicate with the TDK power supply.
Check the following:
- Ethernet connection between the TDK and PLC
- Log out of the TDK web interface
- Power cycle the TDK unit
column9:
F257   TDK Power Supply
Communication Error
Device T8     IP Address: 10.0.1.13

column6:
TDK Power Supply
AC Failure
column7:
The TDK unit is indicating a AC supply issue. This can occur during power cycling of the TDK unit. If the issue is not related to power cycling of the unit, support from TDK may be required.
Consult the TDK user manual for details.
column9:
F258   TDK Power Supply
AC Failure
Device T8     IP Address: 10.0.1.13

column6:
TDK Power Supply
Over Temperature
column7:
The TDK is reporting the an over temperature alarm. Check cooling in and around the TDK and the enclosure.
Consult the TDK user manual for details.
column9:
F259   TDK Power Supply
Over Temperature
Device T8     IP Address: 10.0.1.13

column6:
TDK Power Supply
Fold-Back Protection Fault
column7:
The TDK has reported a fault in the current Fold-Back protection system of the output power. The lights may be drawing more than the current limit that is set on the device. Ensure the current limit is set to 34.0A
Consult the TDK user manual for details.
column9:
F260   TDK Power Supply
Fold-Back Protection Fault
Device T8     IP Address: 10.0.1.13

column6:
TDK Power Supply
Over-Voltage Protection Fault
column7:
The TDK has reported that the output voltage has exceeded the allowable limit. Check that the voltage limit is set to approximately 120.0V. Do not exceed 125V.
Consult the TDK user manual for details.
column9:
F261   TDK Power Supply
Over-Voltage Protection Fault
Device T8     IP Address: 10.0.1.13

column6:
TDK Power Supply
Internal Error
column7: The TDK has reported an internal error. Consult the TDK user manual for details.
column9:
F262   TDK Power Supply
Internal Error
Device T8     IP Address: 10.0.1.13

column6:
TDK Power Supply
Output Current Too Low. One Or More Lights May Be Burnt Out.
column7: The TDK's measured output current is below the threshold. This is an indicator that one or more lamps are not functioning properly and may need to be replaced.
column9:
F263   TDK Power Supply
Output Current Too Low. One Or More Lights May Be Burnt Out.
Device T8     IP Address: 10.0.1.13

column6:
Air Pressure
Should Not Be Ok
column7:
The air pressure sensor is indicating that there is still air pressure in the system when their should not be.
Check the following:
- The electronic dump valve is operating properly and is not overridden
- The safety system is operating properly
- The pneumatics system has not been modified and an air source has not been added after the dump valve.
column9:

Should Not Be Ok
Device H13     Wire # 8327

column6:
Main Enclosure Remote I/O
Communication Error
column7:
The PLC is reporting a communication error with the remote I/O module located in the Main Enclosure. Check the following:
- Ensure the remote I/O module is powered. Check the circuit breaker if it is not.
- Ethernet connection between the remote I/O module and PLC
- Check that there is no other devices on the network with the same IP address
- Power cycle the remote I/O module.
column9:
F459   Main Enclosure Remote I/O
Communication Error
Device L1-1     IP Address: 10.0.1.11

column6:

Communication Error

- Ensure the remote I/O module is powered. Check the circuit breaker if it is not.
- Ethernet connection between the remote I/O module and PLC
- Check that there is no other devices on the network with the same IP address
- Power cycle the remote I/O module.
column9:
F460   HMI Enclosure Remote I/O
Communication Error
Device L1-2     IP Address: 10.0.1.12

column6: Guard Door 1 Opened
column7:
Guard door indicates that it is not fully closed. The door is located on the same side as the main disconnect.
Open and close the door to correct the issue.
If the issue persists, check the alignment of the safety sensor and magnet adjust as required. Inspect the wiring and replace as required.
Note: This signal does not reflect the safety circuit. So it is possible to have a safety circuit issue and not receive this fault.

column6:
Air Pressure 
Should  Be Ok
column7:
The system air pressure is outside of the allowable range. Check the following:
- Dirty or clogged air filters on the air prep unit. Replace as required
- Water in a filter on the air prep unit
- Manual shut off valve is opened
- Electronic dump valve is operating properly
- Incoming air pressure is at 80 PSI or higher
- Pressure regulator is set to 80 PSI
- Leaks in the pneumatic system

Check Connection Between Anybus Module(E40) And
Lamp Power Supply.

- Serial communication between Anybus and XP power supply.
- Power cycle the Anybus unit.
- Power Cycle the XP power supply unit.

column6: Lamps PS #1 AC Failure
column7:
The XP power supply #1 unit is indicating a AC supply issue. This can occur during power cycling of the XP power supply unit. If the issue is not related to power cycling of the unit, support from XP power supply may be required.
Consult the XP power supply user manual for details.

Device T8-1

column6: Lamps PS #1 Over Temperature Fault
column7:

Consult the XP power supply user manual for details.

column6: Lamps PS #1 Vout Over Voltage Fault
